node.text:
Sunday Grandstand 
 
After the Goodwood Festival of Speed a couple of weeks back we headed to the Goodwood Motor Circuit with the Oxford Commission, a Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer - representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. 
 
A few friends showed up and the rain held off. So we made a film. 
 
We hope you like it. 
Sound 👆  
 
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study embody the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence. 
 
Film @thisisgrip 
Driving: @mfranchitti 
Location: @goodwoodmotorcircuit 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #oxford #sundayvibes

node.text:
Over the last 4 days, the first 2 client-specification cars representing the results of the Dynamics and a Lightweighting Study (DLS) have been running at Goodwood Festival of Speed. 
 
Unico is presented in Absinthe Green over Blood Orange, with Nickel polished brightwork. 
 
Oxford is presented in Oak Green Metallic over Bone White, with Champagne polished trim. 
 
Both DLS cars are powered by the 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat six, developed in collaboration with Williams Advanced Engineering - producing 500 HP. 
 
🎥 @thisisgrip

This fantastic set-up was created by the awesome team @doerrgroup, who support Singer’s clients in Germany as members of our global partner network

It’s Monday, so here’s a look back at our Singer Ten Years celebrations at Monterey Car Week in August.

Our aim was not just to assemble some beautiful cars but to create a program that would enable them to be driven and enjoyed.

We began with a drive from Singer HQ near Los Angeles north to Monterey. Behind the wheel were a group of Singer clients, friends and team members. The cars were a chorus of Porsche 911s Reimagined by Singer and assorted sports machines
We took the road less travelled.

Once in Monterey it was a non-stop week taking in:

McCalls Motorworks Revival 
The Dynamics and Lightweighting Study was presented with our friends at @Hagerty

The annual Singer House party 
Invited guests enjoyed the cars (and actual horse power) on display, accompanied by incredible food from the @MichelinGuide chefs.

The Quail, A Motorsports Gathering 
Singer presented five cars from the last ten years, ranging from the first G-series cars, the first 964 restoration, the rise of the Targa and the development of Singer’s Special Wishes services and onto the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. 
Werks Reunion, Monterey
Along with our friends @michelinusa we presented 3 restorations showing what happens when the Singer philosophy #EverythingisImportant meets the @michelin #DevotiontoDetail approach.

Historics, Big Sur, Pebble Beach
After a visit to the Monterey Motorsports Reunion at Laguna Seca, our Singer Experience group took their cars south for another great drive in northern California. The weekend then moved to the famous Pebble Beach concours lawn.

Laguna Seca
The week came to a close on Monday with a private track day. As the track closed, we filled the start - finish straight with air-cooled Porsches for a final technicolour group photograph.

Enormous thanks to everyone who joined us for the experience or came to talk cars and watches with us.
A salute to all the team - both those at Singer base and those on location in Monterey who made this whole operation a success.

Film by @zackj_com

Yesterday we wrapped up our 10th Anniversary trip to Monterey Car Week with a track day at the WeatherTech Raceway Laguna Seca.

Our Singer Experience clients had the track to themselves with technical support from our friends @michelinusa and ran hard all day. The Porsche 911s Reimagined by Singer were joined by a few friends as you’ll see from the film... Our thanks to all our clients for their support over the last decade, all the Singer team in Monterey, Los Angeles, the UK and Geneva who worked to put this week together. 
Likewise we’re grateful for the support of all our amazing partners and everyone who came to see us and talk cars and watches during the last week.

Thanks to @zackj_com and @drewphillipsphoto for the awesome films and images.

node.text:
Singer Reimagined on Saturday 
 
Shown here is the latest work from our watchmaking operations in Geneva, Switzerland. 
 
The Track 1 - DLS Edition has been created to accompany the results of our Dynamics and Lightweighting Study.  
 
It features a forged carbon case with open lugs that echo the ram-air intakes developed for the cars. Grade 5 titanium is used for the bezel, pushers, crown and caseback. Each watch can be personalised to the owner’s vehicle specifications. 
 
This watch continues the evolution of the award-winning Track 1 DNA, first seen in the prototype Track 1 - Launch Edition, worn here by @mfranchitti, head of dynamic development for the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study.  
 
Both watches are powered by the revolutionary, 67-jewel Singer Reimagined Caliber 6361 Agengraphe, enabling a 55-hour power reserve and powering the 60-hour, column-wheel chronograph. 
 
Both cars and watches represent Singer’s ongoing mission: 
A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence 
 
📷 @laurent_xavier_moulin 
📷 @actcreative

Friday Fact: 
 
The central channel in the roof was developed for the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study in collaboration with @williamsadvancedengineering  
 
The feature directs air under the integrated roof / rear window bridge spoiler.  
 
This enables the airflow to stay attached down the rear of the car, aided by contouring of the rear window, and onto the optimised ducktail - with the effect of increasing rear downforce.

Good morning from Monterey Car Week.

Today the first client car representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study is presented at The Quail, a Motorsport Gathering. 

Named the Unico commission by its owner, this Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer is presented in Absinthe Green, with light-ghosted stripes and Blood Orange lettering. 

The car is powered by a 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat six, developing 500 HP at 9000 rpm.

Its companion on the Singer stand is the Hollywood commission. This Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer is presented in Bahama Yellow, with light-ghosted stripes and Forest Green lettering.

This car is inspired by the 1969 911E restored by Singer founder Rob Dickinson in 2003 (shown in the last image). Also painted in Bahama Yellow and daily-driven around the Hollywood Hills, the 1969 car ultimately led to the birth of Singer.

Both cars represent the work of our incredible teams in the U.K. and the US and are a symbol of Singer’s evolution as a company.

To see and hear more about the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study, click the link in our bio.

node.text:
Hollywood to Monterey 
 
The birth of Singer can be traced back to this 1969 911E, restored by Founder, Rob Dickinson back in 2003.  
 
Used as a daily driver around the Hollywood Hills it was fitted with a number of modifications including a 3.0L engine from a 911 SC, a Recaro race seat, central fuel filler and presented in Bahama Yellow with green lettering. The first 2 images here show it captured a few years post-restoration by @mavrocam 
 
Rob would often be stopped while driving the car by people asking if he’d sell it. He never did and owns the car to this day. But those encounters led to the idea of offering other 911 owners services that would enable them to pursue their own vision for their cars.  
 
Fast forward to 2009 and the first Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer was presented during @montereycarweek, at a site close to the well-known @bajacantinacv  - shown in the second two images.
 
This was Singer’s first trip to Monterey. It’s since become a fixture in our annual calendar of events.  
 
We’ll be back this year, including @thequailevents with machines that show the latest work to come from our incredible teams in California and the U.K. - including the first client car representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. We look forward to seeing you there. 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #TheQuail #montereycarweek
